rs, how migrants face exploitation from employers, and more. A must-read for all Americans, The Farmworkers' Journey traces the human consequences of our policy decisions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMigrant agricultural laborersxCalifornia. 0aMigrant agricultural laborersxMexicoxCaliforniaxMexico. 0aMigrant agricultural laborerszCalifornia. 0aMigrant agricultural laborerszMexico. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a21st century american immigration.  a21st century american politics.  aagricultural economy.  aamerican history.  aamerican immigration.  aborder crossing.  acalifornia.  acorporate agribusiness.  ademocracy.  aeconomic globalization.  aeconomics.  afamily.  afarm work.  afarmers and farming.  afarms and farmers.  ahistorical farming practices.  ahuman condition.  aimmigration and emigration.  amexican american border.  amexico.  amigrant workers.  amigration.  anafta.  apolitical debate.  apolitics.  apoverty.  arural.  atransnational corporations.  aunited states of america.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094057440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940574423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520940574/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles